	 <input type=hidden name=quest value=271></td></tr><tr><td colspan=1 style='background: silver;font-size: 9.5px;'>This topic is <a href=/quest.html?quest=271&mid=16990&start=0>1</a>  pages long</td><td style='background: silver;font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=/quest.html?quest=271>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=16990></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f16990><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>A trick for off time players</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Walson</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 6th 7:6 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.37]</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2>I just got the pelt off the Glacial Bear. Sure there are lots of guides like parking a ranger in the cave to check for him. But I found as way to do it that works great for that casual player that is on during the off hours. <br><br>First of all hang around EF for a few days and note who is there. At some point, a high level player will be in the zone, usually a shaman, that is not hunting Ice Giants. Note the time they come in and the time they leave. This gives you a clue to when the bear or PHer will be up during the off times. When they get their pelt they will be gone usually and that is your chance to get the totemic helm.<br><br>Bind yourself near the ice goblin diver near the cave entrance and head off to a place where you can solo effectively and not be too concerned about dying, like the aviaks in SK, even mammoths or icey orcs if a group is there. I got Martar 2x also at level 33 when checking on him, sold one cloak and kept the other for Vox raids later. When that time rolls around, gate back and check the caves out. It took me a while to get the bear but eventually you will even with casual gamer's hours, I usually play less than 4 hours a day for example.<br><br>The bear wanders in one direction and the lich in the other from what I have seen. Scout the cave in a counter clockwise direction. The lich goes in this direction and should he be up, you will be coming up behind him and that gives you plenty of opprotunity to avoid him instead of running head on into him. Since the bear goes the other direction, it makes it easier and safer to scout for him. If you run into a wandering icebone, kill it. Sure you will miss the next spawn BUT that just benefits you in the long run. If the next guy 8 hours later gets the bear, big deal! He will just be gone and lessens the chance that he will be there when you come back.<br><br>This is what worked for me. I started checking on him late in level 32 and when I hit 34 and went and got my spells, the next morning he was up. I didn't even summon a pet, just rooted him and tossed scourge, affliction, and envemoned breathe 2x and he was dead.<br><br>That was the biggest rush I had in the game in a LONG LONG time and considering I also have a 50 warrior, that says something.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td  align=right valign=bottom><span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr></form></table>
